2.06 Jun 15 2002

- Added a deNewline preprocessor that removes trailing \n's. Reflected
  the change in the server code as well. The reason for this is that
  MUAs (like mutt) strip trailing \n's so there's no way to get to
  the original message. This change necessitates upgrade from old 2.x
  agents. [vipul]
- Fixed a bug in Config.pm to use EUID instead of UID to discover
  user's Razor config directory. Thanks to Theo Van Dinter
  <felicity@kluge.net> for the patch. [vipul]
- Fixed a bug in sort in Razor2::String. [vipul]

